dashboard.definition:
{
    "title": "App Compatibility Checker",
    "description": "",
    "inputs": {},
    "defaults": {
        "dataSources": {
            "ds.search": {
                "options": {
                    "queryParameters": {
                        "earliest": "$global_time.earliest$",
                        "latest": "$global_time.latest$"
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "visualizations": {
            "global": {
                "showProgressBar": true
            }
        }
    },
    "visualizations": {
        "viz_3s3WHOZo": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "##  How It Works\n\nThe app runs a custom search command:\n\n| compatibilitycheck tgt_splunk_version=<version>\n\nThe command can also be utilised by the users outside of the dashboard.\n\nIt compares:\n- Installed app versions\n- Declared compatibility metadata from Splunkbase\n- Target Splunk version\n\nResults include:\n- App ID\n- Current version\n- Compatible versions\n- Archive status"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_D0Qg7J2O": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "# **App Compatibility Checker**"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_EjSHMkpB": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "##  Distributed environments\n\nBy default, the App Compatibility Checker can only perform checks on the local host where it is installed. Starting with version 1.1.0, it also supports checks in distributed search environments.\n\nWhen deployed on a Search Head, the App Compatibility Checker can execute checks across the entire distributed setup, including both the Search Head and all connected Indexers."
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_GKEnj417": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "## Known Limitations\n\n- Apps without declared compatibility metadata may appear as incompatible\n- Does not validate custom app code\n- The instance on which the custom command is run requires Internet access."
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_Rgq9ejKK": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "Version: 1.0.0 \n\nLast Updated: February 2026"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_Tw9ApT7t": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "## Maintainer\n\nDaria Garmash\n\nContact: dariagarm.dev@gmail.com"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_gc2NovZ8": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "## Requirements\n\n- Splunk Enterprise 9.2+\n- Python 3"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_hWoiSWP4": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "## Overview \n\nThe App Compatibility Checker identifies installed apps that are not compatible with a selected target Splunk version and displays them on the **Incompatible Apps** dashboard.\n\nIt helps administrators:\n\n- Prepare for Splunk upgrades\n- Detect archived or unsupported apps\n- Reduce upgrade risk\n\nThe app only covers apps not built by Splunk. To check the compatibility status of Splunk-built apps use **Splunk Health Assistant Add-On**."
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_kxtnJgYc": {
            "options": {
                "fontSize": "large",
                "markdown": "##  How To Use\n\n1. Open the \"Incompatible Apps\" dashboard\n2. Select a target Splunk version\n3. Review the results table\n4. Investigate flagged applications before upgrading"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        }
    },
    "dataSources": {},
    "layout": {
        "globalInputs": [],
        "layoutDefinitions": {
            "layout_1": {
